frus:attachment.p:
—Respond to the interest of the Eastern Europeans—as already expressed to us
                        in recent days on a number of occasions—in finding ways to prevent U.S.-Soviet differences from adversely
                        affecting their relations with us and with the West as a whole;

—Preserve, to the degree possible, the progress (in trade, claims
                        negotiations, family reunification, etc.) we have achieved in our relations
                        with the Eastern European countries;

—Reassure the West Europeans by demonstrating that we remain sensitive to
                        their special stake in good East-West relations and their desire to continue
                        an activist policy in Eastern Europe;
